The paper deals with a problem related to social networks and influence diffusion, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SOC). The problem is a well-studied optimization problem in the literature, which suggests that it could also belong to the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) or algorithms and complexity (cs.CC). The authors also mention the concept of degree-bounded graphs, which could indicate that the paper belongs to the category of graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper discusses the performance guarantee of approximation algorithms, which suggests that it could also belong to the category of scientific computing (cs.SI).
